.TH SIMPLE_SHELL 1 "November 2025" "Version 1.1" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
simple_shell \- A simple Unix command-line interpreter.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B hsh
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B simple_shell
is a simple UNIX command line interpreter that replicates basic functionality of the sh shell.
.PP
The shell displays a prompt and waits for the user to type a command. A command line always ends with a new line. The prompt is displayed again each time a command has been executed.
.SH OPTIONS
The shell does not take any options.
.SH COMMANDS
The shell supports the following types of commands:
.TP
.B External Commands
Executes programs found in the PATH environment variable (e.g., /bin/ls, ls, pwd)
.TP
.B Built-in Commands
.RS
.TP
.B exit
Exits the shell
.TP
.B env
Prints the current environment variables
.RE
.SH USAGE
To use the shell in interactive mode:
.PP
.B $ ./hsh
.PP
.B $ ls
.PP
.B file1 file2 file3
.PP
.B $ exit
.PP
To use the shell in non-interactive mode:
.PP
.B echo "ls" | ./hsh
.SH ENVIRONMENT
The shell inherits the environment from the parent process and uses the PATH variable to locate executable programs.
.SH EXIT STATUS
The shell returns:
.TP
.B 0
Success
.TP
.B 1
Error
.TP
.B 2
Incorrect usage
.TP
.B 127
Command not found
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
Execute ls command:
.PP
.B $ ./hsh
.PP
.B $ /bin/ls
.PP
.B file1 file2 file3
.PP
Print environment:
.PP
.B $ env
.PP
.B USER=username
.PP
.B HOME=/home/username
.PP
Exit shell:
.PP
.B $ exit
